trong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-18T03:22:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBaxter\u0027s an idea man, alright, but his characters are pretty one-dimensional and often unlikeable.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-18T05:13:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe ideas are his characters, while people are an expendable lab equipment.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIn best traditions of Jules Verne and others.\u003Cbr\u003E\nOn such space-time scale unlikely one can (and should) distinguish particular persons.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, how many real historical persons could be named \u0022likeable\u0022.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-05-18T05:15:37Z\u0022 title=\u002205/18/2018 05:15  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMay 18, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-18T08:17:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223380907\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175046\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526597459\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022the books can be read in any order because the series takes place in a\u00A0multiverse.\u0022 Sigh\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nChronologically maybe.... but as a reader who has never picked up a book, plot wise, the wrong book wouldn\u0027t make sense to me.\u00A0\u00A0 Where should I start?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-18T11:02:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223381128\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175046\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526631447\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nChronologically maybe.... but as a reader who has never picked up a book, plot wise, the wrong book wouldn\u0027t make sense to me.\u00A0\u00A0 Where should I start?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUltima\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, I think the character of Poole might be a reference to 2001.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-18T14:11:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure, but stories involving several timelines and hops doesn\u0027t sound very well to me. Unless they were co-written, or the connections are clearly only an afterthought, or such. Stories that uses time-travel and timeline-hops only to beat the dead body of a popular series or story\u00A0is usually not good.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-05-18T14:13:57Z\u0022 title=\u002205/18/2018 02:13  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMay 18, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by YNM\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-18T20:04:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223381241\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175046\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526652711\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298447\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022YNM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, YNM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStories that uses time-travel and timeline-hops only to beat the dead body of a popular series or story\u00A0is usually not good.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, its not like that- the universes are very different, and the time travel is the backbone of the books, not a one-time\u00A0device\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-18T21:25:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223381482\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175046\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526673862\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthe\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E time travel is the backbone of the books, not a one-time\u00A0device\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo the entire series is \u0022co-written\u0022 ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"1101","CreatedById":131100,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-19T11:29:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223381128\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175046\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526631447\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/18/2018 at 9:17 AM, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nChronologically maybe.... but as a reader who has never picked up a book, plot wise, the wrong book wouldn\u0027t make sense to me.\u00A0\u00A0 Where should I start?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Destiny\u0027s Children books (Coalescent, Exultant, Transcendent) should make sense by themselves, more or less.\u00A0 I started with the big \u0027Xeelee: Omnibus\u0027 book, which has Raft, Timelike Infinity, Flux and Ring.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-20T20:46:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223381844\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175046\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221526729381\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022131100\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00221101\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/19/2018 at 7:29 AM, 1101 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Destiny\u0027s Children books (Coalescent, Exultant, Transcendent) should make sense by themselves, more or less.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd Resplendent, which finally explains what that pyramid thing is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}